[¬s]"ITBS-Reading
Score revealed significant main effects for both sex and schedule. Children who
attended full-day kindergarten had higher ITBS-Reading Scores than those children
in the half-day program [fl(l,938) = 13.63, p < .01]. The mean Reading Scores on
the ITBS for the full-day and half-day groups were 39.64 and 35.29, respectively.
In addition, girls, overall, had higher reading achievement scores, regardless of
whether they attended full- or half-day kindergarten [7=1(1,969) = 6.93, p < .01]. The
mean Reading Scores on the ITBS for girls (N = 487) was 40.8 while die mean
